    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-02-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-02-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="313"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862S.00/2–2546</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                            State</gloss> to the Chief of the Division of African Affairs</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Villard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-25">February 25,
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Villard</hi>: Referring to the attached letter<note
                        n="36" xml:id="d313fn36">See Mr. Hickerson’s memorandum of February 23, <hi
                            rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> to the British Ambassador, unless there
                    is some very strong reason for the assertion of the right set forth in this
                    letter, I believe it unwise to assert such a right.</p>
                <p>I think that it would establish a precedent for assertion of similar rights by
                    the Soviet Government and the British Government as to Pacific Islands where we
                    do not intend to agree that they are states directly concerned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J[<hi rend="smallcaps">ames</hi>] F. B[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >yrnes</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
